mqtt-grafana
============

Read-only SQLite-to-JSON CGI endpoint for the Freetz web server on port 81.

Installed URL:
  http://fritz.box:81/cgi-bin/mqtt-grafana.cgi

Power dashboard:
  http://fritz.box:81/mqtt-grafana.html

The dashboard displays the current value of obk_wr/power/get and its history
over the last 48 hours. It refreshes every five seconds. The page and endpoint
are served from the same authenticated Freetz web server, so the browser reuses
the port-81 authentication and no credentials are handled by JavaScript.

Parameters:
  from=UNIX_SECONDS       default: now - 3600
  to=UNIX_SECONDS         default: now
  topic=MQTT_TOPIC        optional exact match
  limit=ROWS              default: 2000, capped by menuconfig value
  mode=health             database health/latest timestamp response

Example:
  /cgi-bin/mqtt-grafana.cgi?topic=sensor/temp&from=1700000000&to=1700003600

The endpoint returns timestamps in milliseconds for Grafana and preserves the
original payload. A numeric value field is set when the complete payload is a
valid finite number.

Build notes:
The CGI links libm after libsqlite3 because numeric MQTT payload handling uses
floating-point classification functions such as isfinite(). SQLite headers
come from the target staging directory populated by the declared sqlite
dependency. Changing a menuconfig endpoint option triggers a package rebuild.
